<p>Here is some quick postgis sql that I used to knock up kml of railway station sites in England.</p>

<pre><code>SELECT node.*
FROM
  node_tags tag, nodes node
WHERE tag.k='railway' and tag.v='station'
  and tag.node_id = node.id


SELECT node.*, '&lt;Placemark&gt;&lt;name&gt;' || nametag.v || '&lt;/name&gt;' || ST_AsKML(node.geom) || '&lt;/Placemark&gt;'
FROM
  node_tags tag, nodes node, node_tags nametag
WHERE tag.k='railway' and tag.v='station'
  and tag.node_id = node.id
  and nametag.k='name'
  and node.id = nametag.node_id
</code></pre>

<p>Inspired by this, I have forked <a href="https://github.com/jnicho02/traingraph">traingraph</a> to look at adding my own flourishes.</p>
